  "prompt": "What are the major events that happened in 1997?",
  "response": "1997 was a notable year with numerous significant events across various domains:\n\n1. **Politics and International Relations:**\n   - **Handover of Hong Kong:** On July 1, the United Kingdom returned Hong Kong to Chinese sovereignty, marking the end of 156 years of British rule.\n   - **Tony Blair becomes Prime Minister:** On May 1, Tony Blair led the Labour Party to a landslide victory in the UK general election, ending 18 years of Conservative rule.\n\n2. **Science and Technology:**\n   - **Mars Pathfinder:** NASA's Mars Pathfinder successfully landed on Mars on July 4, and its rover, Sojourner, explored the Martian surface.\n   - **Deep Blue vs. Garry Kasparov:** In May, IBM's Deep Blue chess computer defeated world champion Garry Kasparov in a six-game match.\n\n3. **Disasters:**\n   - **Princess Diana\u2019s death:** On August 31, Diana, Princess of Wales, died in a car crash in Paris, an event which led to a massive outpouring of public grief.\n   - **Beni Isguen massacre:** On January 1-2, in Algeria, 412 people were massacred in an incident attributed to Islamist insurgents.\n\n4. **Culture and Entertainment:**\n   - **Release of Titanic:** James Cameron's epic film \"Titanic\" released on December 19, eventually becoming the highest-grossing film of its time and winning 11 Academy Awards.\n   - **Harry Potter:** J.K. Rowling published \"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone\" (also known as \"Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone\" in the US) on June 26, beginning a global phenomenon.\n\n5. **Economy:**\n   - **Asian Financial Crisis:** Starting in July, the Asian financial crisis commenced with the devaluation of the Thai baht, leading to financial turmoil in many Asian economies.\n\nThese events are just a small snapshot of what occurred in 1997, highlighting a year of significant transitions in political, technological, cultural, and economic spheres.",
